          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-07-19 03:31:51.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6210 utils: Use C99 struct initializers in lustre_fsck.c",
        "message": "LU-6210 utils: Use C99 struct initializers in lustre_fsck.c\n\nThis patch makes no functional changes.  The long_opt_stop and\nlong_opt_query struct initializers in lustre_lfsck.c are updated\nto C99 syntax.\n\nC89 positional initializers require values to be placed in the\ncorrect order. This will cause errors if the fields of the struct\ndefinition are reordered or fields are added or removed. C99 named\ninitializers avoid this problem, and also automatically clear any\nvalues that are not explicitly set.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Steve Guminski <stephenx.guminski@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ie713904f31208447e4d5741023356aa1a37c0ea3\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/27790\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
